						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up near the well at the entrance to the village.</p>						

						<p>1224 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated the cyclic year Tāraṇa, Śrāvaṇa-amāvāsye, Sitavāra. As the epigraph can be assigned to the 13th century, the details may be taken to correspond to 1224 A.D., August 16, Friday.</p>						

						<p>It records the death of a Jaina devotee named Satyaṇṇa by the rite of <hi rend="italic">Sanyasana.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
